subproject.description:
The global financial crisis has also impacted Uzbekistan, with a great number of migrants returning to their home country adding to the unemployed numbers, causing ancillary problems. Thus, on the one hand, there is need for improved coordination and monitoring of employment policies, legislation, and their gendered impact by involved actors. On the other hand, there is a need to boost innovative job creation and income generation initiatives in rural areas, especially targeting women. 
The Initiation Plan aims at piloting social enterprises for women’s employment (with professional and social handicaps) in rural areas as well as developing a full scale project document targeting supporting policy making and enabling legislative and institutional environment to promote equal rights and opportunities for stereotype free choice of employment by women and men.
